content.content: yep, my first time watching the anime a couple weeks ago, I almost gave up with how slow the first few episodes are. but after episode 4 it just clicked, now it's one of my favorite anime. I am so glad I watched the anime and the movie, in fact I wish I'd watched them sooner but I'm kinda glad this was my first watch. If I had watched it when I was younger I doubt I would've understood it or even liked it, this anime speaks to me in a very particular way. The Loneliness, the Sadness, the Lack of Purpose, the Grief, the Loss, everything. It perfectly encapsulates my own lack of purpose, loneliness, sadness and resolves it in a natural feeling way. Goddamn it I want to punch Gilbert at the end, I understand how she feels too well, but I also understand him as well. I can't blame him, I can't get mad at him because I know those same feelings of resentment. I may or may not have watched the anime and then just skipped to the last movie so I have a bit of catching up to do, probably a lot more crying to do as well, but I love this anime so i still love  crying to it. But hey, at least it shows that I still can.
